1. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - This paper discusses the formalization of UML 2.0, which is a software engineering tool. 
2. cs.PL (Programming Languages) - The paper discusses a semantic model for UML, which involves defining a language for describing software systems. 
3. cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) - The paper discusses the use of a system model as the basis for a semantic model, which involves defining logical relationships between different components of the model. 
4. cs.DB (Databases) - The paper discusses the definition of a structural data model, which is relevant to database design. 
5. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper mentions the possibility of object-oriented, possibly distributed systems, which suggests a connection to distributed computing.
